        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 21 at 8:31PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 831 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ragland, or 12 miles northwest of West End-Cobb Town. This
thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lincoln, Riverside, Ragland, Ohatchee, Honda Manufacturing Of
Alabama, Bynum, Alexandria, Neely Henry Lake, Logan Martin Lake,
Anniston Army Depot, Neely Henry Dam, and Eastaboga.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
